parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake System Failure (Hydraulic and Caliper Issues)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the brakes to overheat, leading to a loss of braking power, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: brake pedal goes to the floor
vigorous pumping required to activate brakes

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake caliper can cause the brakes to fail, leading to a loss of braking power, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: brake pedal goes to the floor
vigorous pumping required to activate brakes

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected activation of the auto park brake while driving can cause the vehicle to come to an abrupt stop, potentially leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The auto park warning light illuminates
the vehicle comes to an immediate stop
the vehicle is unable to move until the drive shaft is removed.
